      <div class="msgContentFrame">From what I've seen, the main crafts for the finished product: <br /> <br /><b>Lances :</b> Mainly carpenter, but it seems some lances are finished with goldsmith because of metallic decorations.(ex: <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/item.html?ffxivitem=4080203" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/item.html?ffxivitem=4080203"> Brass Spear </a>, but it also &quot;seems&quot; it needs a carpenter made lance as its base ) <br /> <br /><b>Armors :</b> Looking at the favored bodies, it seems that the cycle is weaver-leathercraft-armorer up until lv50 at least 3-4 times. <br /> <br />This holds true for the body armor. As for other slots, you can remove one of the crafts (ex: I haven't found leg armor requiring armorer), but the cycle seems to be maintained. <br />(nb: exception is for shoes where it seems some of them are made from carpentry.) <br /> <br />As for sub crafts, with the known recipes, I would say everything else except cooking.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>As long as Guu is having fun, everything is Ok. <br /> <br />FFXI :  Goudaba @Valefor <br />FFXIV : Goudaba Wynarv @Kashuan</div></div>
