      <div class="msgContentFrame">For armor I'd focus on armorer primarily, leatherworking secondary, thirdly weaver.  The higher rank armor is mostly metal (cuirass, hauburgeon, celata, sollerets, etc.)  A lot of the other pieces are leather (leather leggings, leather fingerless gloves, pot helms, etc).  And of course there are cloth pieces they can use as well (shirts, acton, and I believe some cloth is needed for crafting other stuff as well).  Of course goldmsithing and blacksmithing help with making some components that you need as an armorer. <br /> <br />Ultimately though, you can't make anything from scratch with just 1 crafting class, and to make your own gear you will need you crafting much higher than your Lancer rank.  For example, I just bought bone scale mail for my Lancer.  It's rank 14, but you need Armorer 27 and Leatherworking 11 to make it. <br /> <br />For weapons you need carpentry primary, goldsmith secondary.  Carpentry crafts the lances, but of course you need blacksmithing to make some parts.  Goldsmithing is used to add brass to a bronze spear and make a brass spear. <br /> <br />Personally, I'm raising armor/leather/carpenter/gold just enough to be able to reliably repair my gear.  I don't think that using a crafting class to make your own gear is feasible unless you plan on having your crafting class be much higher than your fighting class.</div>
