      <div class="msgContentFrame">To repair weapons: Goldsmith (Brass Spear, Jarl Guisarme and Banneret Lance, Goldsmith also upgrade them from the normal Bronze Spear, Guisarme and Iron Lance) and Carpenter for the rest. <br /> <br />To repair armours: Leatherworker if you're going to wear Leather based (Jacket, Skirt, Leggings, Leather belt, Mitt etc.), Armourer if you wear Metallic based (Scale, Haubergeon, Cuirass, Gauntlets, Sabatons etc.), you will have have full set of Leather and Metallic as a LNC. There is a full set of Cloth (Acton, Trousers, Sarouel, Turban, Halfgloves, Sash etc.) as well, but it is not as good for fighting.  <br /> <br />To be able to craft both your weapons and armours as you go is not realistic unless you play 72 hours a day. Well, that's also unrealistic.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1807831.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
